{"lemma": "حَقٌّ", "slug": "حَقٌّ", "root": "ح.ق.ق", "root_slug": "ح-ق-ق", "root_link": "/words/roots/ح-ق-ق", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "حَقّ", "root": "حقق", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 247}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 7, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 28}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n8564"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8C%D9%91"}}, "translations": {"en": "right", "fa": "حق", "ur": "حق", "tr": "hak", "id": "hak", "bn": "হক", "es": "derecho", "fr": "droit", "de": "Recht", "ru": "право", "zh": "权利"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be true, to be confirmed"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be right, to be correct"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be necessary, to be obligatory, to be imperative"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be adequate, to be suitable, to be appropriate, to be fitting", "examples": [{"text": "وَلَقَدْ بَعَثْنَا فِي كُلِّ أُمَّةٍ رَّسُولًا أَنِ ٱعْبُدُوٱ ٱللَّهَ وَاجْتَنِبُوٱ الطَّاغُوتَ فَمِنْهُم مَّنْ هَدَى اللَّهُ وَمِنْهُم مَّنْ حَقَّتْ عَلَيْهِ الضَّلَالَةُ فَسِيرُوٱ فِي الْأَرْضِ فَٱنْظُرُوٱ كَيْفَ كَانَ عَاقِبَةُ الْمُكَذِّبِينَ", "english": "And we certainly sent into every nation a messenger [saying] “worship God and avoid the idol”. And among them were those whom God guided, and among them were those upon whom error was deservedly enacted. So proceed through the earth and see how was the end of the deniers."}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be due"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to ascertain, to make sure"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to recognize, to identify"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be necessary, to be obligatory, to be imperative"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be adequate, to be suitable, to be appropriate, to be fitting"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be due"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of حُقَّ (ḥuqqa) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of حَقَّ (ḥaqqa) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "equity"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "truth"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "correctness, right"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "rightful possession, property"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "right"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "proper manner"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "reality"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "rights, claims, legal claims", "tags": ["in-plural"], "examples": [{"text": "الْحُقُوق (al-ḥuqūq)", "english": "law, jurisprudence"}]}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "true, authentic, real"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "right, fair and reasonable"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "valid, sound, correct"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "jar"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "pitcher"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "hollow, cavity"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "socket of a joint"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "plural of حُقَّة (ḥuqqa)", "tags": ["form-of", "plural"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From the root ح ق ق (ḥ q q). Compare Hebrew חוק (ḥóqq, “law”), Classical Syriac ܚܘܩܐ (ḥuqqā, “rule”), Ge'ez ሐቀቀ (ḥäḳäḳä, “to fasten”), Tigrinya ሓቂ (ḥaqqi, “truth”).\nPerhaps related to حَجَّ (ḥajja, “to convince with legal arguments; to make the pilgrimage to Mecca”) and words corresponding to this root in the other Semitic languages.\n\nUsing the root ح ق ق (ḥ q q) via the idea of “fitting” parts."}, "ipa": ["/ħaq.qa/", "/ħuq.qa/", "/ħaqq/", "/ħuqq/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n8564", "headword_ar": "حَقٌّ", "root": "Hq", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baATilN", "text_ar": "بَاطِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[used as a subst. and as an epithet or act. part. n.]: (S, Msb, K:) or, as an inf. n. [and used as a simple subst.],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "buTolaAnN", "text_ar": "بُطْلَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and as an act. part. n., and a simple epithet,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baATilN", "text_ar": "بَاطِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Kull.) [As a subst.,] its primary signification is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Suitableness to the requirements of wisdom, justice, right,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rightness, truth, reality,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fact;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the exigencies of the case;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as the suitableness of the foot of a door in respect of its socket, for turning round rightly: (Er-Rághib, TA:) [and particularly] the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "suitableness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a judgment, and of what involves, or implies, a judgment, [i. e., of a saying, and a religion, and a persuasion, or the like, (as will be shown by one of the explanations of its meanings as an epithet,)]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to reality"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fact;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "suitableness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of reality or fact"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to a judgment:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Kull:) [the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "state,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "quality,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "property, of being just, proper, right, correct,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "true; justness, propriety, rightness, correctness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "truth; reality,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fact;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "state,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of being established,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "confirmed, as a truth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fact; of being necessary, requisite,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "unavoidable; of being binding, obligatory, incumbent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "due:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(as shown above: see 1, first sentence:)] and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "existence"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in relation to substances, absolutely: and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "everlasting existence"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in relation to God]: (Kull:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HuquwqN", "text_ar": "حُقُوقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HiqaAqN", "text_ar": "حِقَاقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": it has no pl. of pauc. (TA.) As an act. part. n. and a simple epithet, it is applied to a judgment [as meaning]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "suitable to reality"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fact;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and to a saying, and a religion, and a persuasion, considered as involving, or implying, such a judgment: (Kull:) to that which is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "suitable to the requirements of wisdom, justice, right,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rightness;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as when one says that every act of God is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~", "text_ar": "حَقّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": to a belief, in a thing,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "suitable to the reality of the case;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as when one says that belief in the resurrection is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~", "text_ar": "حَقّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and to an action, and a saying,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "accordant to what is requisite"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obligatory, in quality and measure and time;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as when one says that the action of another is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~", "text_ar": "حَقّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and that his saying is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~", "text_ar": "حَقّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Er-Rághib, TA:) [thus it signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "just, proper, right, correct,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "true; authentic, genuine, sound,"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 608}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "valid, substantial,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "real; established,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "confirmed, as a truth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fact:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "necessary, requisite,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "unavoidable:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "binding, obligatory, incumbent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "due:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] also the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "necessarily-existing by his own essence"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[applied to God; as an epithet of Whom it has other meanings assigned to it by some, as will be seen below]: and anything"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "existing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of an objective kind: (Kull:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "existing as an established fact,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "truth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so as to be undeniable."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) In the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA Eabodu A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "هٰذَا عَبْدُ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaq~a laA AlbaATila", "text_ar": "الحَقَّ لَا البَاطِلَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is 'Abd-Allah, truly; not falsely"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], the article"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al", "text_ar": "ال"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is prefixed as it is in the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^arosalahaA AlEiraAka", "text_ar": "اَرْسَلَهَا العِرَاكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but sometimes it is dropped, so that one says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~FA laA baATilFA", "text_ar": "حَقًّا لَا بَاطِلًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Sb, TA.) And in the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laHaq~u laA A=tiyka", "text_ar": "لَحَقُّ لَا ا=تِيكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", a form of oath, the nom. case is used without tenween; but when the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "l", "text_ar": "ل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is dropped, one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~FA laA A=tiyka", "text_ar": "حَقًّا لَا ا=تِيكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, TA:) [the latter means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Truly I will not come to thee:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the former seems to be best explained by what here follows:] accord. to the A,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laHaq~u laA A^afoEalu", "text_ar": "لَحَقُّ لَا اَفْعَلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laHaq~u A@ll~`hi laA A^afoEalu", "text_ar": "لَحَقُّ ا@للّٰهِ لَا اَفْعَلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The truth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "existence, of God"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is that by which I swear,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will not do"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "such a thing]; the affixed noun ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "All~`h", "text_ar": "اللّٰه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] being suppressed, and meant to be understood. (TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaq~u biyadiY", "text_ar": "الحَقُّ بِيَدِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The right is mine"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaq~u maEiY", "text_ar": "الحَقُّ مَعِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The right is with me"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaq~u Ealayoka", "text_ar": "الحَقُّ عَلَيْكَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The right is against thee,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "which last is often used as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thou art in fault,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the wrong,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] are said by one disputing, or contending, for a thing. (TA.) [And in like manner one says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaq~u biyadika", "text_ar": "الحَقُّ بِيَدِكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEaka", "text_ar": "مَعَكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Thou art in the right,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaq~u", "text_ar": "الحَقُّ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY~a", "text_ar": "عَلَىَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I am in the wrong."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAna *`lika Einoda Haq~i laqaAHihaA", "text_ar": "كَانَ ذٰلِكَ عِنْدَ حَقِّ لَقَاحِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqaAHihaA", "text_ar": "لَقَاحِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hiq~i", "text_ar": "حِقِّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That was on the occasion of the establishment of the fact of her conception,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pregnancy."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, K, * TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA AlEaAlimu Haq~a AlEaAlimi", "text_ar": "هٰذَا العَالِمُ حَقَّ العَالِمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA AlEaAlimu", "text_ar": "هٰذَا العَالِمُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jid~a AlEaAlimi", "text_ar": "جِدَّ العَالِمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is the learned"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "man,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the extremely learned"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "man. (Sb, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~u EaliymK", "text_ar": "حَقُّ عَلِيمٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Very"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "extremely"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "knowing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ham p. 139.) [Respecting the expressions"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaq~u Alyaqiynu", "text_ar": "الحَقُّ اليَقِينُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~u", "text_ar": "حَقُّ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alyaqiyni", "text_ar": "اليَقِينِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yqn", "text_ar": "يقن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b2-  [From the primary and general signification, explained in the first sentence of this paragraph, are deduced several particular meanings here following.] ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Equity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "justice."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b4-  [The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "right mode,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "manner, of acting"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "being."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Veracity"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in discourse."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Prudence."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.) ―         -b7-  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A right,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "due, of any kind: a just claim: a desert,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thing deserved: anything that is owed;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a fee, hire,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pay,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a price: a duty; an obligation:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] the sing. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HuquwqN", "text_ar": "حُقُوقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, K.) [You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA Haq~iY", "text_ar": "هٰذَا حَقِّى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is my right,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "due,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c. And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA Haq~N liY", "text_ar": "هٰذَا حَقٌّ لِى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is a right,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "due, belonging to me;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing due,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "owed, to me:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "this is a duty to me."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA Haq~N EalaY~a", "text_ar": "هٰذَا حَقٌّ عَلَىَّ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is a right,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "due, the rendering of which is binding, obligatory,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "incumbent, on me:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "this is my duty."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "And hence,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~u AlT~ariyqi", "text_ar": "حَقُّ الطَّرِيقِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The duty that relates to the road:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Trq", "text_ar": "طرق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~apN", "text_ar": "حَقَّةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a more particular, or peculiar, or special, term. (S, K.) You say, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*ihi Haq~atiY", "text_ar": "هٰذِهِ حَقَّتِى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is my particular,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "peculiar,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "special, right"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "due"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.: but it is explained as] meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~iY", "text_ar": "حَقِّى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*ihi Hiq~atiY", "text_ar": "هٰذِهِ حِقَّتِى", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is my just,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "necessary,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "incumbent, right"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "due"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c. (K.) ―         -b8-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A share,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "portion;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEoTi kul~a *iY Haq~K Haq~ahu", "text_ar": "اَعْطِ كُلَّ ذِى حَقٍّ حَقَّهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Give thou to every one to whom belongs a share,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "portion, his share,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "portion, that is appointed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "assigned, to him."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b9-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Property: a possession."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b10-  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An appertenance."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "Hence the pl.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HuquwqN", "text_ar": "حُقُوقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies The"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maraAfiq", "text_ar": "مَرَافِق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "appertenances,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "conveniences, such as the privy and the kitchen and the like,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] of a house. (Msb, TA.) ―         -b11-  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A necessary,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "requisite, thing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b12-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an event, that is decreed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "destined."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.) It is said to have this meaning in the Kur [xv. 8], in the words,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA nunaz~ilu AlmalaAy^ikapa", "text_ar": "مَا نُنَزِّلُ المَلَايِكَةَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_il~aA biAlHaq~i", "text_ar": "اـِلَّا بِالحَقِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "We send not down the angels save with that which is decreed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "destined"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (TA:) or, as some say, it means here"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "revelation:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ksh, Bd:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "punishment."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ksh, Bd, Jel.) ―         -b13-  [And hence,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Death."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) So accord. to some in the Kur [1. 18], where it is said,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wa jaA='ato sakorapu Almawoti biAlHaq~i", "text_ar": "وَ جَا=ءَتْ سَكْرَةُ المَوْتِ بِالحَقِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And the confusion of the intellect by reason of the agony of death shall come with death:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but other and obvious meanings are assigned to it in this instance]. (TA.) ―         -b14-  [As an epithet,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaq~u", "text_ar": "الحَقُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is one of the names of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "God:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or one of the epithets applied to Him: (K:) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the Really-existing; whose existence and divinity are proved to be true:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAth, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the Creator according to the requirements of wisdom, justice, right,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rightness."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Er-Rághib, TA.) ―         -b15-  It is also applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The Kur-án."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b16-  And to ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The religion of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "El-Islám."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaqiyqN", "text_ar": "حَقِيقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in two places.       -A3-  And see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAq~N", "text_ar": "حَاقٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in two places."}], "source_refs": ["S", "Msb", "K", "Kull", "TA", "Ksh", "Bd", "IAth"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translation